@startuml
title Viaverse Payment / Wallet — Component Diagram

component "KMP / Next.js Client\nPayment screen\nWallet UI\nResult screen" as Client
component "API Gateway / App BFF\nPayment API\nWallet API" as BFF
component "PaymentController\nProviderCallbackController" as Controller
component "Payment Use Cases\nCreatePaymentSession\nHandleCallback\nRefund\nReleasePayout" as UseCases
component "Payment Policies\namount/currency\njob state\nrefund/payout auth\nidempotency" as Policies
component "Ports\nPaymentProvider\nWalletProvider\nPaymentRepo\nOutboxPort" as Ports
component "Provider Adapters\niyzico\nStripe\nMasterpass" as Providers
component "marketplace-service\njob/quote state\npayout block state" as Marketplace
database "PostgreSQL\npayment_session\nstored_payment_method\ncallback_record\ncommission_ledger" as DB
queue "Kafka / Outbox\nPaymentAuthorized\nRefundIssued\nPayoutReleased" as Kafka
component "Admin BFF\nrefund/payout actions\nreason + audit" as Admin

Client --> BFF : HTTPS
BFF --> Controller : REST
Controller --> UseCases : command
UseCases --> Policies : validate
Policies --> Ports : ports
Ports --> Providers : adapter calls
Policies --> Marketplace : job/quote checks
Ports --> DB : persist
UseCases --> Kafka : outbox events
Admin --> UseCases : admin commands
Providers ..> Controller : callbacks

note bottom
Payment domain never stores raw card data.
Provider SDKs live only in provider adapters behind PaymentProvider/WalletProvider ports.
end note
@enduml
